        eu_protection_title: 'The EU is preparing to transition from temporary protection for Ukrainians to more stable legal statuses',
        eu_protection_description: 'The Council of the European Union has approved a recommendation for a phased exit from the temporary protection regime, which currently applies to Ukrainians displaced by the war, and has been extended until March 4, 2027.\n\nRecommendations include:\n‚Ä¢ Granting national residence permits to those who work, study, are in a family, or meet other established conditions.\n‚Ä¢ The possibility of transitioning to statuses under EU laws, especially for highly qualified specialists.\n‚Ä¢ The organization of voluntary return to Ukraine when the situation allows, with support and coordinated conditions between member states.\n‚Ä¢ The obligation to inform displaced persons about their current rights, how benefits will change, and what will happen after exiting temporary protection.\n\nThe EU communiqu√© emphasizes that this initiative is not aimed at accelerating the termination of protection, but rather at preparing the infrastructure and legal framework to ensure a normatively correct, fair, and gradual transition from temporary protection to more permanent conditions.',
