        // Unity Day of Ukraine translations
        unity_day_title: 'January 22 ‚Äî Unity Day of Ukraine',
        unity_day_text: 'This is the day when Ukraine proved to the whole world:\nwe are united.\nUnited in language and culture.\nUnited in the pursuit of freedom.\nUnited from the Carpathians to Donbas, from Polissia to Crimea.\n\nOn January 22, 1919, the Act of Union of the UPR and ZUNR was proclaimed ‚Äî a historic decision that enshrined a simple but extremely powerful idea: Ukraine is one and indivisible.\n\nToday, unity is not just about borders.\nIt\'s about mutual support.\nAbout shared responsibility.\nAbout people who stick together despite war, loss, and pain.\n\nOur unity is the greatest strength that the enemy fears.\nAnd it is what brings victory closer.\n\nTogether ‚Äî strong. Together ‚Äî unbreakable. Together ‚Äî Ukraine. üíôüíõ',
        rozkolyada_title: '‚ú® Rozkoljada. Letzter Weihnachtsklang ‚ú®',
        rozkolyada_text: 'You are cordially invited to share the joy of Christ\'s birth with us üéÑ\nThe last chords of the holidays ‚Äî at a joint celebration of Ukrainian choirs in Linz.\n\nYou can look forward to:\nüåü joint prayer\nüåü caroling and Christmas songs\nüåü Ukrainian souvenirs\nüåü refreshments, hot mulled wine and traditional punch\n\nMay the light of the Star of Bethlehem warm hearts, unite the community and fill this day with joy, peace and hope ü§ç\n\nüìç ALTER DOM, DOMGASSE 3, 4020 LINZ\nüóì 01.02.2026\n\nWe look forward to seeing you and your whole family!',
